ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would say it is a difficult course, but ultimately rewarding. I would recommend the course to anyone interested in Medieval literature.
Yes, I would recommend this course. Approached properly, it can be rewarding with a minimum of frustration.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I feel that I learned even more than I was expecting to learn of Old French: I feel equipped to go on to read other literature in this language.

This course did not at all contribute to my dissertation. It did however contribute greatly to my general knowledge in my discipline. I have already started making links with course I have taken thatover other centuries. I'm really glad I took this course.

This course opens up a lot of doors for my own research, as I can confidently approach thousands of new texts when planning a dissertation, without needingEnglish editions or even French critical editions. My new knowledge of Old French will be an invaluable tool.
